			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't remember much about CRT these days, but isn't every CRT TV has a built-in degaussing coil and automatic degauss circuit? Also, it is understandable if a system tuned up for one position can be detuned by rotating it, but I have doubts that a system that was initially tuned up for 90 degree orientation will have some speical problems that would require special tech solution compared to another orientation.</div>

