						<div class="postbody">I have never used a color CRT produced in the 1980s or later that did not have a degaussing coil. Ones with failed posistors though, that's something I have come across, rendering the degaussing circuit unusable.<br /><br />While an LCD does not face this issue relating to color purity, common peasant-grade LCD panels will suffer serious quality issues seeing as most popular computer displays right now are TN panels.</div>

